THOUSANDS of participants braved the rain to walk in memory of those they had lost and in support of their loved ones suffering from cancer at this year&rsquo;s Algoa FM Big Walk for Cancer.Summerstrand was a wave of pink on Saturday, with about 11 000 people doing the 5km walk.They were joined by the Premier Phumulo Masualle, Nelson Mandela Bay Mayor Athol Trollip, Health MEC Dr Pumza Dyantyi and Miss South Africa Ntandoyenkosi Kunene. It was the 18th annual Big Walk, held in partnership with the provincial health department. Phumla Cakwebe (47) said: &ldquo;I was diagnosed with breast cancer in 2008. This day reminds me of the journey I had to take.&rdquo;Algoa FM manager Dave Tilman said: &ldquo;It is important to raise awareness about cancer as it affects everyone. This year we have three beneficiaries &ndash; CHOC, the Igazi Foundation and Cansa.&rdquo;